org.apache.myfaces.trinidad.share.io
Interface InputStreamProvider

public interface InputStreamProvider

InputStreamProviders encapsulate a single target file. An InputStreamProvider is used to get an inputStream, cache results and see if the file has been modified. (There's no real requirement that there be a physical file at the target location).

getDisplayName

java.lang.String getDisplayName()

getIdentifier

java.lang.Object getIdentifier()
Returns an identifier object that uniquely identifies the target location. If two providers return equal identifiers, that is, given: 
   Object identifierA = providerA.getIdentifier();
   Object identifierB = providerB.getIdentifier();
... then: 
   if (identifierA.equals(identifierB)) ...
then the two providers must point to the same location.
